  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesize that the T1 Dixon post-Gadolinium and T2 Dixon sequences will
      show good diagnostic performances for active sacroiliitis compared to the reference test
      (Short tau inversion recovery) and clinical-biological criteria, which will allow a better
      diagnosis of active sacroiliitis
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
